Lectures give an overview of the core questions and main concepts of parasitism as a life phenomenon. The course topics cover transition to parasitic lifestyle, forms and stages of parasitism, adaptations of parasites, and evolutionary development of the relationship between a parasite and a host.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to develop a general understanding of parasitism as a widely spread from of life in nature. It gives an overview of parasite diversity and helps to understand the evolutionary importance of parasites.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  .The course gives an understanding of the role of parasites in evolution and their impact on human societies. Introductory lectures give an overview of the taxonomic distribution and ubiquity of parasites. Researchers of specific fields introduce the parasites of fish, birds and mammals. The second part of the course helps to understand the importance of parasites as evolutionary and ecological force. Article seminars introduce newest and most intriguing scientific findings. Practical part gives an opportunity to try your hand in parasitology methods.
